cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of recognizing pedestrian attributes from far-view image frames, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an alternative approach to the conventional SVM-based method, which involves exploiting the context of neighboring pedestrian images, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the informativeness of background and foreground features for attribute recognition, which suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
